WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Character design is one of the most exciting aspects of illustration.

2
00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:08.000
Creating memorable, expressive characters requires understanding

3
00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:12.000
anatomy, personality, and visual storytelling principles.

4
00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
Every character should have a clear purpose and personality

5
00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
that comes through in their design. Shape language is crucial

6
00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.000
for character design - angular shapes suggest aggression or energy,

7
00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
while rounded shapes feel friendly and approachable. Understanding

8
00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
basic anatomy helps you create believable proportions, even

9
00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
when stylizing your characters dramatically. Silhouette strength

10
00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
ensures your characters are instantly recognizable from any angle.

11
00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.000
We'll explore different character archetypes and how to

12
00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
convey personality through posture, clothing, and accessories.

13
00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
Color choices and facial expressions are powerful tools

14
00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:56.000
for character development. This lesson will give you

15
00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:00.000
a systematic approach to designing characters that resonate

16
00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.000
with viewers and serve your storytelling goals effectively.

17
00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:08.000
Ready to bring your characters to life? Let's start designing.